data.title: El Checo en México: Happiness of having a classic Beetle, concerns about the future of Czech goods
data.meta_description: Volkswagen Beetle. It´s not it, folks. It´s him. The vehicle with great V. My dad in law lent me one of his beloved vehicles of his fleet. ...
data.text:
Acerca de mí

Lukas

was born in Ceske Budejovice, in the south of the Czech Republic. His university studies began at the Prague´s University of Police where he obtained undergraduate Bc. degree in Security studies. He was lucky enough to study some of his undergraduate courses in the UK, at the University of Central Lancashire, Preston. From August 2008 is residing in Mexico where he initiated in January 2009 his MA degree program in Estudios Internacionales at the ITESM University, Campus Mexico City. In June 2009 studied one of the ITESM compulsory subjects at the Georgetown University, Washington D.C. Lukas is an authorized tour guide for the region of Czech Republic and for the Czech tourists abroad. He has also obtained highly valued qualification of the Official tour guide for the City of Prague. He likes history, in particular the contemporary one, travelling, languages, collective sports, world politics and loves his country. This blog will tackle the problematics of his daily life in Mexico City, his feelings, ideas that just cross his mind and actually everything that will happen in such a wonderful, but sometimes tough country, which Mexico - without doubts - is.
